Experts fear two-inch-long Asian hornets could be heading to Britain .
They pick off bees as they leave hive until colony is so exhausted the hornets can move in and ransack it .
One Asian hornet can kill 40 bees in a minute, while a handful can destroy a hive of 30,000 bees .
UK beekeepers have been sent email alerts by Defra asking them to be on the look-out for the menaces .